`MemoryIOStream::Seek` looks like this:
```c++
aiReturn Seek(size_t pOffset, aiOrigin pOrigin) {
    if (aiOrigin_SET == pOrigin) {
        if (pOffset >= length) {
            return AI_FAILURE;
        }
        pos = pOffset;
    }
    else if (aiOrigin_END == pOrigin) {
        if (pOffset >= length) {
            return AI_FAILURE;
        }
        pos = length-pOffset;
    }
    else {
        if (pOffset+pos >= length) {
            return AI_FAILURE;
        }
        pos += pOffset;
    }
    return AI_SUCCESS;
}
```

I think, that the comparisons with `pOffset` should be done using `>` instead of `>=`.

Otherwise the following function calls do not behave symmetrical:
* `memoryIOWrapper.Seek(0, aiOrigin_END)`
* `memoryIOWrapper.Seek(length, aiOrigin_SET)`

Both function calls should seek to position "`length`", but only the first function call succeeds.

